<br>
I've read the patch message and wonder about the changes to damage.  I've focused primarily on being a dual wielder (Langseax/PGT) and wonder how I'm affected.  [BTW - at the advice of esteemed members here, I did go out and max 2hs as well and am working on the others.  I own a Axe of Iron Black which I use almost equally now]<br>
<br>
I usually use the dual wield when I want a higher taunt and we've got plenty of damagers in the group.<br>
<br>
Did they just make this even less effective damage wise??<br>
<br>
 <p>
Captain Kalkoric Toraknan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukupafrostheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupa FrostHeart</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/20/00 8:02:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flash.net/~coop37/objects/beer.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> 40+ delay weapons both one handed and 2 handed got a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> small</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> boost in damage. 27 and under delay two hand weapons got a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> big</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> reduction in damage.<br>
<br>
No big swing in weapon balance. Basically they wanted to make the mosscovered branch less powerful and they accomplished that. No big change for you as a dual wielder. <p><body link="green" vlink="green"><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=3 COLOR="green"><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF=http://www.eqforge.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=3242>Kupa FrostHeart</a><BR></FONT><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=2 COLOR="yellow">Kupa's muscles ripple in anticipation of the flames to come...</FONT></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukalkorac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalkorac</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/00 6:38:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> But my langseax has a delay of 26 - I've not done much more than 10-12 damage with it (non-crit) and now you imply that I'll be doing less??<br>
<br>
 <p>
Captain Kalkoric Toraknan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukupafrostheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupa FrostHeart</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/00 8:05:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flash.net/~coop37/objects/beer.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> First of all, your Langseax has a delay of 23, not 26 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
