And Hugs to Vengie :-)<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unorok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ironcross.org/images/ironcross.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/00 10:47:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> I am curious about this as well...<br>
<br>
As you are all aware (Mainly because I point it out at every opportunity <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) I use an Oggok Cleaver which has 60 delay. I have noticed very little change as a result of this last patch.<br>
<br>
I have also noted no real haste reduction - but then again I use a Runebanded Girdle and not a FBSS.<br>
<br>
For the damage I have noticed my Best hit without being a critical hit has gone up from 206 to 209 - this could be pure coincidence.<br>
<br>
The thing I was watching is the &quot;Magic Number&quot; - the number that while I am not sure exactly what it means I know I hit that Number more then ANY other number. For example the Magic number for my Oggok Cleaver at level 51 is 103. When I parse out a Nights adventuring to see my stats I notice that I have anywhere from 400 to 1000 times MORE hits at that number then any other number. While the graph is mapped few low hits and more medium hits this one number usually has more hits in it then all the other numbers combined. I was sort of expecting this number to raise if they raised the damage modifier on Slow 2 handed weapons, this number has not moved.<br>
<br>
So my guess would be that they modified the limit on Max Damage possible by these weapons and not general damage.<br>
<br>
Again this is nothing more then a Blind geuss on my part.<br>
<br>
How this will affect you if this is true... Well about 3 to 5 percent of the time we hit for max damage - Maybe less - the only time this new modifier will affect us is during this 3 to 5 percent we will achieve a few more points of damage.<br>
<br>
If they had modified the general damage done then this &quot;Magic Number&quot; would have moved up a few points and the the overall effect would be more damage done. I do not feel this is the case.<br>
<br>
For example<br>
My best non crit was 206 - I would get a 206 hit three out of (lets guess) every one Hundren hits (3%) So with the max Damage raised by 3 In one hundred Hits I will actually be doing 9 more points of damage total.<br>
<br>
Now had they moved the &quot;Magic Number&quot; instead of max damage possible. Out of 100 Hits I would land 50 of them on this magic number(while the remaining 50 are spread from 1 damage to 206) if this number had been moved up 3 points then out of 100 Hits I would now be doing 150 points more in 100 hits then I was doing before patch.<br>
<br>
Either way total Damage dealt would only move slightly but as you can see there is a drastic difference in what they could have done.<br>
<br>
My geuss is they moved the max damage which means - Jack and Sh..  well you get the idea<br>
