</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukupafrostheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupa FrostHeart</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/00 11:38:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flash.net/~coop37/objects/beer.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> Your magic number should have moved up 3 pts by my calculations, cleaver is 44/60 yes? The current theory, which seems to be holding for the most part, is the high delay bonus = (del-35)/3, which would be 3 for the cleaver.<br>
<br>
I gained a measly one point with my Skarlon. On the other hand you should get a 37 pt delay bonus for a weighted axe *chuckles*<br>
<br>
The easiest way to observe the difference is to look at the difference between your critical message and the related damage message (directly below it). That difference is your level bonus + your delay bonus. Check it with a cleaver and then with a lower delay 2 hander, like Nathsar Greatsword or Axe fo the Iron Back, etc and notice the difference <p><body link="green" vlink="green"><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=3 COLOR="green"><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF=http://www.eqforge.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=3242>Kupa FrostHeart</a><BR></FONT><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=2 COLOR="yellow">Kupa's muscles ripple in anticipation of the flames to come...</FONT></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unorok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ironcross.org/images/ironcross.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/21/00 12:38:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Explain Damage Changes Please</span><hr size=1> After 2 Nights of Parsing my &quot;Magic Number&quot; is exactly what it was prior to the patch and my average damage as well as Damage per second have remained within the same margin of tolerance I had prior to the patch.<br>
<br>
Hmm as for checking the Crits - honestly my Crits varied depending on how much damage the crit did - the more damage the larger the gap between the shown message and the actual damage. But even this only ranged from 10 to 14 points.<br>
<br>
So a 300+ point crit the difference for me was around 14 points but for Crits around 100 the difference was 10 points<br>
<br>
I always wondered why there was a difference between the crit message and the actual damage.<br>
<br>
This does explain alot but doesn't explain why the difference based on the higher damage - perhaps it is a problem only assoiciated with the extremely large numbers produced by the Cleaver... I will have to experiment with some other weapons...<br>
